 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search DevOps Automation Engineer Genentech 955 reviews South San Francisco, CA 94080 Genentech 955 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description The Genentech Research and Early Development organization seeks a talented and motivated Automation Engineer to join us in supporting scientific software development and high performance computing. Your responsibilities will focus on collaborating with software developers as well as cloud and platform engineers to automate infrastructure, tools, platforms and processes using a variety of technologies. You will develop and maintain patterns of usage and translate them into a catalogue of building block templates and complete working processes that tie together terrestrial and public cloud resources. These automated environments and processes will conform to security requirements while offering functionality and flexibility. You will join a team of infrastructure engineers and IT support professionals with skills and experience in both technology and life sciences. Together, you will have the opportunity to build a modern cloud-based environment to help propel Genentech's drug development ambitions by automating tasks making them easy, reliable and consistent when deploying them. 
The Genentech Research and Early Development organization is a world-class research and drug development organization. Staffed with some of the world's most brilliant scientists, bioinformaticians, and computational researchers, the breadth and depth of scientific expertise across a broad range of disciplines can't be overstated. Encouraging an open, academic-like atmosphere and frequently publishing in top-tier, peer reviewed journals, scientists work with a variety of technologies including high performance computing (HPC), cloud platforms, modern software development tools, petabyte-scale storage, machine learning, and artificial intelligence. 
Responsibilities 
Collaborate with business and IT colleagues to develop and maintain automation patterns 
Create catalogues of templates that automate infrastructure and software elements 
Collaborate with cloud and platform engineers to build software development pipelines 
Provide guidance to new and existing development groups on automation 
Rigorously document solutions and provide knowledge transfer to operational teams 
Technically lead and mentor other team members, delegating work, and tracking progress 
Qualifications: 
6+ years developing, building, and deploying into cloud infrastructure environments 
Recent experience supporting CI/CD development and production pipelines at large scale 
Demonstrated expertise with one or more of Terraform, Ansible, Jenkins, Chef or Puppet 
Strong skills with a programming language using modular, reusable code methodologies 
Expertise in AWS networking, IAM, security and managed services a must 
Excellent code and usage documentation as well as knowledge transfer skills required 
Strategic mindset and ability to identify challenges and design solutions a must 
Experience leading technical teams and supervising work on larger projects 
A focus on solution delivery, with excellent time management and organization skills 
Excellent interpersonal skills with your own team, technical IT partners, and stakeholders 
